# Backend README.md

```markdown
# 🏥 MediCloud – Backend

A secure RESTful API built with PHP and MySQL following a Controller-Service architecture. The backend supports multi-tenant healthcare operations with JWT authentication, RBAC, CSRF protection, and secure REST APIs.

---

## 🚀 Features

- RESTful API
- Multi-Tenant Architecture
- JWT Authentication
- Refresh Token Support
- CSRF Protection
- Role-Based Access Control
- CRUD APIs
- Secure Password Hashing
- MySQL Database
- Modular Architecture
- CORS Support
- API Validation

---

## 🛠 Tech Stack

- PHP
- MySQL
- Apache
- JWT
- REST API
- Composer (Optional)

---

## 📂 Project Structure

app/
│
├── Config/
├── Controllers/
├── Database/
├── Helpers/
├── Middleware/
├── Models/
├── Routes/
├── Security/
├── Services/
└── Utils/

public/
│
├── index.php
└── .htaccess


---

## ⚙ Installation

Clone the repository.

git clone <repository-url>


Import the database.

Configure


app/Config/config.php


Run Apache and MySQL.

Backend URL


http://localhost/new-MVP/MVP-server/public


---

